WEBVTT

00:01.084 --> 00:02.670
Ah.

00:02.795 --> 00:04.797
Man, it's freezing in here.

00:04.839 --> 00:08.007
I mean, how long are they
gonna go at it today?

00:08.759 --> 00:10.761
I haven't eaten anything
since this morning.

00:10.803 --> 00:12.471
I'm starving.

00:13.263 --> 00:15.516
What should I eat
when I get home?

00:24.650 --> 00:25.985
[groans]

00:26.735 --> 00:28.403
[MAN] No, look, I told ya,

00:28.445 --> 00:29.947
bigger is better.

00:30.238 --> 00:33.701
If we're gonna make it fight,
heavier is the best choice.

00:33.742 --> 00:36.453
Well, then go find it
and call back later.

00:37.412 --> 00:38.622
Huh?

00:38.664 --> 00:39.957
No guard?

00:40.916 --> 00:42.376
Did he go somewhere?

00:42.417 --> 00:45.044
Hell of a time
to take a bathroom break.

00:45.086 --> 00:46.213
[gasps]

00:46.254 --> 00:47.631
[groans]

00:47.673 --> 00:48.757
[Megumi exhales]

00:51.092 --> 00:52.887
Hey, look at this!

00:52.928 --> 00:54.262
Huh?

00:54.304 --> 00:55.931
You think it eats fish sausage?

00:55.973 --> 00:56.932
[MAN IN T-SHIRT] Wait a minute.

00:57.182 --> 00:58.392
That thing was
in the tournament, wasn't it?

00:58.433 --> 00:59.434
Oh, here you go, little Panda...

00:59.476 --> 01:01.269
Hey, doofus,
pandas don't eat meat.

01:01.311 --> 01:02.396
They eat bamboo.

01:02.437 --> 01:03.856
[both men groan]

01:03.898 --> 01:06.025
[PANDA] Well,
this Panda eats fish sausage.

01:08.235 --> 01:10.738
No cameras on
the emergency stairs.

01:11.989 --> 01:13.072
Yo!

01:14.533 --> 01:17.076
You sure about this?
It's a risky plan.

01:17.703 --> 01:19.538
It could cause you
trouble later on.

01:20.497 --> 01:22.541
[PANDA] It's fine, it's fine.

01:22.583 --> 01:25.084
We just need to secure
the area by the door.

01:35.512 --> 01:37.138
Oh, no, it's Kirara!

01:37.180 --> 01:39.098
What are they doing
away from Hakari?

01:41.268 --> 01:42.519
It's Panda.

01:43.020 --> 01:45.522
And that spiky-haired kid.

01:45.856 --> 01:47.942
If Panda helped him
sneak in here,

01:47.983 --> 01:51.486
that means
he's with Jujutsu High?

01:51.528 --> 01:54.281
Which means Yu-ie is
with Jujutsu High too.

01:54.322 --> 01:55.741
And then that means...

01:56.157 --> 01:59.078
Kin is in danger.

01:59.118 --> 02:01.329
Look, boss,
I need to tell you something.

02:01.371 --> 02:04.165
[cell phone ringing]

02:04.207 --> 02:06.209
[MEGUMI] Demon Dog: Totality!

02:06.543 --> 02:07.711
[grunts]

02:07.753 --> 02:09.088
[Panda grunts]

02:09.922 --> 02:11.256
[roars]

02:15.970 --> 02:17.136
Fushiguro?

02:18.472 --> 02:19.598
[grunts]

02:20.975 --> 02:22.935
[MEGUMI]
My Demon Dog was thrown back?

02:22.977 --> 02:25.353
No, judging
from what Panda said,

02:25.395 --> 02:27.106
it couldn't get
close enough to them.

02:29.858 --> 02:31.610
[all gasp]

02:31.652 --> 02:34.321
[KIRARA] There, Panda
and the other two are marked.

02:34.362 --> 02:36.364
[PANDA] The monitor room!

02:36.406 --> 02:39.034
Kirara's planning on
heading back to Hakari!

02:39.409 --> 02:42.830
[Panda panting]

02:42.913 --> 02:45.457
Wait, Kirara!
We're not your enemies.

02:45.499 --> 02:48.293
We just want
to ask Hakari for a favor!

02:48.335 --> 02:51.630
I don't believe that.
I'm disappointed in you, Panda.

02:51.672 --> 02:52.923
This is pathetic!

02:53.172 --> 02:55.676
I can't even get close to you
while walking or running!

02:55.717 --> 02:57.594
[both panting]

02:59.013 --> 03:01.598
[MEGUMI] So Kirara
can't get close to us, either?

03:01.640 --> 03:03.558
[Panda panting]

03:03.600 --> 03:04.726
[PANDA] Fushiguro?

03:05.144 --> 03:06.854
[MEGUMI] It's more than just
being able to approach them.

03:06.895 --> 03:09.064
I can't separate
from Demon Dog, either.

03:09.106 --> 03:11.108
What kind
of a curse technique is this?

03:11.733 --> 03:12.943
[grunts]

03:12.985 --> 03:14.903
- Listen!
- Save it, kid!

03:14.945 --> 03:17.196
My passion has gone cold!

03:18.281 --> 03:20.450
[♪ opening theme song playing]

04:51.458 --> 04:53.543
[♪ tense music playing]

04:55.796 --> 04:57.338
[MEGUMI] We're at a stalemate.

04:57.380 --> 04:58.423
Perfect.

04:58.924 --> 05:00.050
Kirara!

05:00.092 --> 05:02.136
We're not currently
with Jujutsu High.

05:02.594 --> 05:04.846
You know what Tokyo is like
right now, don't you?

05:06.640 --> 05:07.724
Mm.

05:08.433 --> 05:10.102
[MEGUMI] The barriers
that sprung up in each region

05:10.144 --> 05:11.436
are related, as well.

05:11.561 --> 05:14.397
It was an unprecedented attack
of jujutsu terrorism!

05:14.898 --> 05:16.399
We need Hakari's help.

05:17.109 --> 05:19.611
Well, you're the ones who
excluded us in the first place.

05:19.653 --> 05:21.155
You reap what you sow.

05:21.655 --> 05:23.865
[MEGUMI] I told you,
we're not with Jujutsu High.

05:23.907 --> 05:26.201
What happened between you
and the higher-ups?

05:26.243 --> 05:28.078
[PANDA] They fought
with the conservatives.

05:28.120 --> 05:30.247
Of course,
their idea of "conservative"

05:30.289 --> 05:33.332
goes beyond just their policy
toward the regulations.

05:33.374 --> 05:37.087
They have set ideas of what
and what not jujutsu should be.

05:37.378 --> 05:39.840
Kugisaki's technique
is a good example.

05:39.881 --> 05:41.591
That's the kind
of classic jujutsu

05:41.633 --> 05:43.177
the conservatives prefer.

05:43.218 --> 05:45.053
Not stuff
like the cursed videos

05:45.095 --> 05:46.721
that were popular a while back.

05:46.763 --> 05:49.141
As time goes on,
even jujutsu incorporates

05:49.183 --> 05:50.600
more new technologies.

05:50.934 --> 05:52.853
But some of those
new techniques are bound

05:52.894 --> 05:54.813
to make the conservatives fussy.

05:55.563 --> 05:58.192
Kin's technique is
a perfect example of that.

05:58.608 --> 06:00.986
That's why those
stupid higher-ups lost.

06:01.569 --> 06:02.696
Here's an idea.

06:02.737 --> 06:04.239
Why don't you have Satoru Gojo

06:04.281 --> 06:06.116
save your asses for you,
like always.

06:06.158 --> 06:09.036
If you have him, why do you
need us so badly, huh?

06:09.077 --> 06:11.370
The answer is,
you're lying about needing us.

06:11.412 --> 06:14.333
Which means you're here
for some other reason, right?

06:16.251 --> 06:18.670
Satoru Gojo
has been sealed away.

06:19.171 --> 06:20.672
It's the reason we lost.

06:33.018 --> 06:34.728
[PANDA] Oh, no.

06:34.769 --> 06:36.813
[BOTH] They don't believe us!

06:36.897 --> 06:39.233
[PANDA] Well,
I can understand that.

06:39.274 --> 06:42.861
[MEGUMI] But this person
is the one closest to Hakari!

06:43.778 --> 06:44.821
Rabbit Escape!

06:46.240 --> 06:47.324
[KIRARA] Bunny rabbits?

06:47.406 --> 06:48.992
[MEGUMI]
If we can just convince them,

06:49.034 --> 06:51.661
negotiations with Hakari
will go more smoothly.

06:54.664 --> 06:55.999
Acrux?

06:58.501 --> 06:59.753
Gacrux?

07:01.046 --> 07:02.589
[KIRARA]
That's a lot of bunnies.

07:02.630 --> 07:04.299
What's he up to?

07:04.341 --> 07:06.385
My technique
marks cursed energy.

07:06.425 --> 07:08.595
So it treats sorcerers
and their shikigami

07:08.636 --> 07:10.264
as the exact same thing.

07:10.638 --> 07:12.431
At this rate,
the bunnies will be drawn to him

07:12.473 --> 07:14.017
like that doggy was,

07:14.059 --> 07:16.061
and he'll be crushed
under his own shikigami

07:16.103 --> 07:17.812
until he suffocates.

07:29.574 --> 07:30.867
Panda, what happened?

07:30.909 --> 07:32.451
Tell me about Rabbit Escape!

07:32.493 --> 07:34.453
They were almost
as cute as I am!

07:34.495 --> 07:35.663
I don't mean how they looked!

07:35.872 --> 07:38.375
What were they able
to approach and not approach?

07:38.417 --> 07:41.253
Oh. They were able to
get up to that second floor

07:41.295 --> 07:42.503
with no problem!

07:42.545 --> 07:45.048
But they couldn't get
near Kirara or the door!

07:45.548 --> 07:47.968
Panda, do you have
anything written on your body?

07:48.009 --> 07:49.719
A star and a name somewhere?

07:50.929 --> 07:54.766
[gasps] Oh! I-M-A-I?

07:54.808 --> 07:56.059
[MEGUMI] I should have one too.

07:56.101 --> 07:59.104
- [PANDA] Imai? It says "Imai!"
- There.

07:59.146 --> 08:00.981
[MEGUMI]
Just like on the rabbits.

08:02.481 --> 08:04.276
It's probably on Totality, too.

08:04.318 --> 08:06.527
I don't know anything
about their technique.

08:06.569 --> 08:07.821
Wait a minute.

08:08.738 --> 08:09.823
I've got it!

08:10.157 --> 08:12.367
This technique is
based on a constellation!

08:12.617 --> 08:14.035
[KIRARA]
Anyone looking at the sky

08:14.077 --> 08:15.287
could figure that part out.

08:15.329 --> 08:17.372
[MEGUMI]
And the constellation is...

08:21.918 --> 08:23.462
the Southern Cross.

08:29.134 --> 08:30.427
Shit!

08:30.469 --> 08:32.595
We both let it
show on our faces.

08:32.637 --> 08:35.056
He gave me a look like,
"Seriously?"

08:35.098 --> 08:37.976
He just guessed my technique
was based on the Southern Cross,

08:38.018 --> 08:39.769
but he wasn't sure about it.

08:39.811 --> 08:42.147
Then I gave him
that same stupid look.

08:42.189 --> 08:43.898
I confirmed it for him.

08:45.275 --> 08:47.361
If he figures out any more
of my technique,

08:47.402 --> 08:49.528
he'll be able
to enter the monitor room.

08:49.570 --> 08:51.239
I have to stop him here.

08:51.781 --> 08:53.492
[MEGUMI]
Back in a stalemate again?

08:56.286 --> 08:58.288
But was it really
the Southern Cross?

08:59.538 --> 09:01.166
Tsumiki taught me that.

09:01.875 --> 09:03.793
I don't really know
about the other ones.

09:03.835 --> 09:06.880
But isn't the Southern Cross
a four-star constellation?

09:06.921 --> 09:08.547
[PANDA] Fushiguro?

09:09.257 --> 09:11.592
[MEGUMI] Looks like I can
still get close to Panda.

09:12.511 --> 09:13.970
Panda,
do you happen to know

09:14.012 --> 09:16.264
if the Southern Cross
has four stars in it?

09:16.306 --> 09:18.641
Uh, well, I mean, it's a cross.

09:19.267 --> 09:21.269
So there has to be
at least four.

09:26.024 --> 09:28.360
Kirara's technique
must apply one of the stars

09:28.402 --> 09:30.320
in the Southern Cross
to each of us.

09:30.862 --> 09:32.655
And I thought it might
use that to force us

09:32.697 --> 09:34.699
to maintain a certain distance.

09:34.741 --> 09:36.575
But Kirara can
approach the door,

09:36.868 --> 09:38.828
and you and I can
approach each other.

09:39.496 --> 09:41.748
[PANDA] So maybe
Kirara and the door stars

09:41.789 --> 09:42.874
are repelling ours,

09:43.041 --> 09:45.210
like opposite magnets
push each other away?

09:45.752 --> 09:47.170
No, that doesn't sound right.

09:47.212 --> 09:49.089
If that were true,
Kirara would just flee

09:49.130 --> 09:50.090
into the monitor room.

09:50.131 --> 09:51.258
[PANDA] You're right.

09:51.674 --> 09:54.094
And if they hugged the inside
of the door, we'd be stuck.

09:55.762 --> 09:57.722
Hey, wait a minute.
What about this?

09:58.181 --> 10:00.683
Star A is able
to approach Star B,

10:00.725 --> 10:02.477
but B can't approach A.

10:02.852 --> 10:06.189
Each star has only one other
star they're compatible with.

10:06.231 --> 10:09.109
And they cannot approach
any other star but that one,

10:09.150 --> 10:10.735
like in rock-paper-scissors.

10:11.652 --> 10:13.363
But you and I can
approach each other.

10:14.364 --> 10:16.575
We have no problem
moving toward one another.

10:16.950 --> 10:18.201
So that's a no?

10:20.161 --> 10:22.372
[MEGUMI] Maybe it's
more like a stamp rally.

10:22.830 --> 10:24.541
Where you have to
follow a set route

10:24.583 --> 10:26.293
and approach each one in order.

10:26.793 --> 10:29.129
And things with the same star
get drawn together.

10:30.213 --> 10:31.506
That's interesting.

10:31.548 --> 10:33.133
But what if
the sorcerer isn't counted

10:33.174 --> 10:35.302
as one of the stars
in the constellation?

10:35.343 --> 10:36.803
That can't be the case.

10:36.844 --> 10:39.638
Because they were forced
to stay away from Demon Dog.

10:40.140 --> 10:41.891
Just look at Kirara.

10:41.933 --> 10:44.436
They're obviously on high alert
about our next move.

10:44.478 --> 10:46.563
Because they're afraid
that while they're not looking,

10:46.605 --> 10:47.772
we manage to get what we need

10:47.814 --> 10:49.732
in order to enter
that monitor room.

10:50.150 --> 10:52.986
So forget four stars,
there's at least five or more.

10:53.027 --> 10:54.112
Right.

10:54.154 --> 10:56.490
If my stamp rally theory
is correct,

10:56.531 --> 10:57.991
then with only four stars,

10:58.032 --> 11:00.619
we should be able
to approach Kirara freely.

11:00.910 --> 11:02.162
But we can't.

11:02.203 --> 11:03.913
So there has to be a fifth star.

11:03.955 --> 11:05.457
And that's the star
we have to pass through

11:05.499 --> 11:07.459
to reach Kirara and that door.

11:08.376 --> 11:10.504
What if there are
six or seven stars?

11:10.545 --> 11:11.630
Yeah, well, I'm really hoping

11:11.670 --> 11:13.423
that's not what
we're up against.

11:13.465 --> 11:15.674
It's confusing enough
with five stars.

11:16.134 --> 11:18.011
[KIRARA] If they figured it out,

11:18.052 --> 11:20.138
then I have to attack!

11:21.348 --> 11:23.433
[car alarm wailing]

11:26.894 --> 11:28.647
- [groans]
- [MEGUMI] Panda!

11:31.024 --> 11:33.734
[PANDA] I'm okay.
Don't worry about me.

11:33.776 --> 11:35.111
Just go!

11:35.153 --> 11:36.695
And find that star!

11:38.323 --> 11:40.825
[groans, grunts]

11:40.867 --> 11:42.952
Hey, don’t go
throwing cars right now!

11:42.994 --> 11:44.037
[Panda grunts]

11:46.122 --> 11:47.582
[groans]

11:47.624 --> 11:50.293
[MEGUMI] The same Imai star
on you is on that car!

11:50.335 --> 11:52.003
If you throw it,
it'll just come back.

11:52.045 --> 11:54.673
Or pull you toward it
like Demon Dog did to me!

11:55.465 --> 11:56.966
They probably
have to touch the target

11:57.008 --> 11:58.468
to plant a star on them.

11:58.843 --> 12:00.470
No, that can't be right!

12:00.512 --> 12:02.889
Kirara hasn't touched me
or Rabbit Escape!

12:02.930 --> 12:04.807
They only touched Demon Dog.

12:04.849 --> 12:07.768
Meaning,
Kirara isn't tagging objects.

12:07.810 --> 12:09.646
They're tagging cursed energy!

12:09.688 --> 12:11.606
In order to tag doors and cars,

12:11.648 --> 12:13.816
they might need someone
to imbue cursed energy

12:13.858 --> 12:15.360
into them ahead of time.

12:19.406 --> 12:20.699
I knew it!

12:21.949 --> 12:24.827
The car has residual cursed
energy from someone else!

12:25.370 --> 12:27.872
If the technique
doesn't cover a wide range,

12:27.914 --> 12:30.124
then traces
of the other star should be!

12:30.166 --> 12:32.586
[Panda exclaiming]

12:33.044 --> 12:34.087
[grunts]

12:35.547 --> 12:36.923
[groans]

12:41.553 --> 12:43.930
[MEGUMI] There! The fifth star!

12:44.889 --> 12:46.849
I don't see any more
residual cursed energy

12:46.891 --> 12:48.685
from anyone other than us.

12:48.727 --> 12:51.187
Kirara's already marked
their own cursed energy,

12:51.563 --> 12:53.064
so they can't use it
to mark objects

12:53.106 --> 12:55.609
with the same Acrux star
that they labeled me with.

12:56.067 --> 12:57.694
Meaning, they can't
launch things at me

12:57.736 --> 12:59.404
like they did with that car.

13:01.698 --> 13:04.576
Once I touch that,
I can approach Kirara!

13:05.702 --> 13:08.204
[NARRATOR] Fushiguro's
hypothesis was correct.

13:08.996 --> 13:11.708
Kirara's cursed technique,
Love Rendezvous,

13:11.750 --> 13:13.042
assigns one of five stars

13:13.084 --> 13:15.128
to the cursed energy
of their targets,

13:15.169 --> 13:17.297
using the Southern Cross
as a base.

13:18.548 --> 13:20.841
For one star
to approach another,

13:20.883 --> 13:23.344
it must follow
a predetermined order.

13:23.386 --> 13:26.847
Things marked with the same star
are attracted to each other.

13:28.933 --> 13:30.351
Very impressive.

13:30.393 --> 13:33.438
I can't believe you actually
figured out my technique.

13:33.896 --> 13:35.148
Panda! Here, catch 'em!

13:35.189 --> 13:37.776
Mm... [grunts]

13:39.319 --> 13:42.530
[grunts]

13:47.952 --> 13:49.078
[both gasp]

13:49.412 --> 13:51.498
[NARRATOR]
That order was nearest

13:51.539 --> 13:53.500
to the farthest star.

13:53.541 --> 13:55.293
Constellations may look flat,

13:55.335 --> 13:57.545
but they do,
of course, have depth,

13:57.587 --> 14:00.799
And each star has
a different distance from Earth.

14:00.839 --> 14:02.801
You're so smart,
I bet you thought

14:02.841 --> 14:05.886
there's no way I could throw
objects at you any longer.

14:05.928 --> 14:07.639
Well, I can just
lift the Ginan star,

14:07.681 --> 14:09.599
placed on my own cursed energy,

14:09.641 --> 14:11.726
and mark things
with the same Acrux star

14:11.768 --> 14:13.144
that I put on you!

14:19.400 --> 14:21.319
[gasps] What?

14:22.362 --> 14:23.613
How?

14:23.655 --> 14:25.365
Where did it come from?

14:26.783 --> 14:27.950
The boy,

14:27.992 --> 14:30.495
he never dismissed
his doggy shikigami.

14:30.537 --> 14:32.747
Did he figure out which
of the same tagged objects

14:32.789 --> 14:34.123
would be drawn to the other?

14:34.541 --> 14:37.335
Then he put a wall between
himself and the shikigami

14:37.418 --> 14:40.213
so the shikigami would be
drawn into the wall.

14:40.254 --> 14:41.506
Then he unleashed the doggy

14:41.548 --> 14:43.675
when I was in a line
between them.

14:44.843 --> 14:47.261
Love Rendezvous, cancel.

14:49.972 --> 14:51.349
[grunts]

14:54.811 --> 14:56.062
[Kirara yelps]

15:06.113 --> 15:07.532
Please, Kirara.

15:07.574 --> 15:08.907
Just hear us out.

15:22.213 --> 15:23.882
[KIRARA]
Did you really do that?

15:23.922 --> 15:25.884
Set me up with my own technique?

15:25.924 --> 15:27.343
There's no way
you could have known

15:27.427 --> 15:29.679
if you or the doggy would get
pulled toward the other.

15:29.721 --> 15:32.348
I took a gamble,
but now I know for certain.

15:32.807 --> 15:34.308
The one
with the greater cursed energy

15:34.350 --> 15:35.769
pulls the other towards it.

15:36.644 --> 15:39.188
The first time I was
pulled into Demon Dog.

15:39.230 --> 15:40.899
But when I strengthened
my cursed energy

15:40.939 --> 15:43.150
to guard against
your incoming attack,

15:43.192 --> 15:44.819
the opposite happened.

15:45.779 --> 15:47.697
You're really just a first-year?

15:47.739 --> 15:49.741
You aren't cute at all,
you know.

15:54.203 --> 15:55.538
[MEGUMI] Please.

15:55.580 --> 15:56.873
We don't have time.

15:57.206 --> 15:58.458
Please hear us out.

16:00.543 --> 16:02.503
[Kirara sighs] All right, fine.

16:02.545 --> 16:04.714
- [Yuji groans]
- [crashing]

16:05.632 --> 16:06.716
[both gasp]

16:06.758 --> 16:08.342
[scraping]

16:08.384 --> 16:09.469
[BOTH] Hm?

16:10.804 --> 16:12.054
[MEGUMI] Itadori?

16:12.096 --> 16:13.306
[YUJI] Fushiguro.

16:13.347 --> 16:15.224
[groans] Panda.

16:15.266 --> 16:16.935
Stay out of this.

16:23.274 --> 16:24.776
[grunts]

16:24.818 --> 16:25.944
[growls]

16:28.905 --> 16:30.949
[KINJI] Underestimating me, huh?

16:33.326 --> 16:34.452
[all gasp]

16:35.870 --> 16:37.831
[KINJI]
What is it with this kid?

16:37.872 --> 16:40.917
He's not even trying
to dodge my punches.

16:40.959 --> 16:42.794
You crazy or what?

16:43.419 --> 16:45.672
[YUJI] This isn't like
the fight in Shibuya.

16:46.547 --> 16:49.133
This is me
looking Hakari in the eyes

16:49.634 --> 16:51.469
until he accepts me.

16:52.470 --> 16:54.305
I won't dodge anymore.

16:54.347 --> 16:56.098
I won't fight back.

16:57.099 --> 16:59.352
Not until he caves.

16:59.393 --> 17:00.728
How's this?

17:00.812 --> 17:02.897
I'll listen
to what you have to say.

17:02.939 --> 17:05.065
For as long as
you remain standing!

17:05.107 --> 17:06.818
[KIRARA] Kin, baby, stop!

17:06.860 --> 17:08.695
These kids just want your help.

17:08.736 --> 17:10.697
Just hear them out, okay?

17:10.738 --> 17:13.491
I just said I would, didn't I?

17:19.079 --> 17:20.665
Okay, Itadori.

17:20.707 --> 17:21.958
Why me?

17:22.625 --> 17:25.127
This is the first time
we've met, right?

17:25.628 --> 17:28.214
So why did you come to me?

17:28.882 --> 17:30.591
It's because of your strength.

17:30.633 --> 17:32.802
All of my friends
told me you were strong.

17:34.303 --> 17:36.764
Of course. Figures.

17:36.806 --> 17:39.392
When one sorcerer
asks another for help,

17:39.433 --> 17:40.643
it's an understood agreement

17:40.685 --> 17:43.061
that they're asking him
to risk his life.

17:43.938 --> 17:46.566
So if I'm gonna
throw my chips in with you,

17:46.607 --> 17:48.902
you better show me
that you have a passion

17:48.943 --> 17:50.737
worth risking my life for!

17:50.778 --> 17:52.530
Right here and now.

17:52.572 --> 17:54.448
Yet you offer me nothing,

17:54.490 --> 17:56.993
saying you're just here
following orders.

17:57.035 --> 17:58.661
What the hell, old man Yaga

17:58.703 --> 18:01.039
should be weeding out
losers like you!

18:04.792 --> 18:06.586
I don't have any passion.

18:07.045 --> 18:08.004
Huh?

18:08.046 --> 18:09.630
I'm nothing but a cog.

18:10.339 --> 18:12.592
A cog in a sorcerer's machine.

18:12.633 --> 18:14.635
That keeps exorcising curses.

18:15.678 --> 18:16.721
A cog.

18:17.597 --> 18:20.600
Wait, wait, wait.
Are you for real?

18:21.183 --> 18:23.061
'Cause that's damn boring.

18:23.394 --> 18:25.438
Stop it! Enough, Itadori!

18:30.026 --> 18:31.903
[Kinji grunts]

18:40.787 --> 18:42.580
[KINJI] Hurts, doesn't it?

18:43.081 --> 18:45.165
You know what Gojo once told me?

18:45.708 --> 18:48.502
That my cursed energy
was coarser and grittier

18:48.544 --> 18:50.504
than anyone else
he's ever known.

18:51.923 --> 18:53.257
Are you dead yet?

18:55.760 --> 18:56.928
Hey, Panda!

18:56.970 --> 18:58.679
- Who?
- You and Sea Urchin Head!

18:58.721 --> 19:00.932
Take Itadori's body
and get lost!

19:00.974 --> 19:02.600
And don't ever come back!

19:04.184 --> 19:05.686
[gasps]

19:06.938 --> 19:09.273
[KINJI] He took
three unguarded blows.

19:09.315 --> 19:12.026
Plus I hit him with a whole lot
of punches before, too.

19:12.068 --> 19:14.487
What the hell
are you made of, kid?

19:14.528 --> 19:16.072
I'm nothing but a cog.

19:16.572 --> 19:18.658
But cogs have a function,
you know.

19:19.617 --> 19:22.244
My function is
to keep exorcising curses.

19:23.037 --> 19:25.247
Because I need you
to achieve that,

19:26.206 --> 19:28.793
then I'll play along
until you agree to it.

19:42.932 --> 19:44.517
Kinji Hakari.

19:45.267 --> 19:46.727
What's your function?

19:47.561 --> 19:49.396
[KINJI] This kid.

19:49.438 --> 19:53.026
So this is what
a cog's passion looks like.

19:56.403 --> 19:58.656
Fine. I'll keep punching.

19:58.698 --> 20:00.116
[KIRARA] Kin, baby.

20:00.533 --> 20:02.326
I can tell you're all heated up.

20:03.119 --> 20:04.620
[gasps]

20:06.664 --> 20:10.376
[KINJI] It's true.
The fever never lies.

20:13.129 --> 20:14.797
Get down here, you three.

20:14.839 --> 20:15.840
[Panda whimpers]

20:16.757 --> 20:18.176
Let's cut a deal.

20:20.136 --> 20:22.847
[MEGUMI] Uh,
you mean it's resolved?

20:22.889 --> 20:25.141
Did you just convince him
to do that?

20:25.183 --> 20:27.643
- Mm-hm.
- Thank you for saving his life.

20:27.685 --> 20:28.728
All good.

20:29.227 --> 20:31.564
We may hate the upper brass
at Jujutsu High,

20:31.605 --> 20:32.732
but it's undeniable,

20:33.024 --> 20:35.693
Kin's fever burns hottest
when he's helping others.

20:38.112 --> 20:40.156
- [YUJI] Ow!
- [PANDA] Hmm?

20:41.574 --> 20:45.619
Ding-dong! Ding-dong, ding-dong,
ding-dong, ding-dong, ding-dong!

20:45.661 --> 20:46.704
[all gasp]

20:46.746 --> 20:47.914
[KOGANE] Please be advised.

20:47.955 --> 20:49.207
Effective immediately,

20:49.331 --> 20:51.918
a player has added a new rule
to the Culling Game.

20:51.959 --> 20:53.293
Rule number nine!

20:53.335 --> 20:55.713
Players will know
each other's information,

20:55.755 --> 20:57.506
first names, last names,

20:57.548 --> 20:59.092
number of points accumulated,

20:59.133 --> 21:00.760
current colony,
and number of rules

21:00.801 --> 21:02.511
added to the game by you.

21:07.975 --> 21:10.686
You have gained five points
for a kill.

21:10.728 --> 21:12.730
[HAJIME]
You're damn right, I killed him.

21:17.026 --> 21:20.238
Not a single one of these guys
was strong enough.

21:20.278 --> 21:23.908
It really was so much better
400 years ago.

21:23.950 --> 21:25.743
[growls]

21:25.785 --> 21:28.286
Where are you, Sukuna?

21:32.666 --> 21:35.753
[KOGANE] You have
exceeded 200 points.

21:35.795 --> 21:38.089
Would you like
to consume 100 points

21:38.131 --> 21:40.591
by adding a rule
to the Culling Game?

21:40.633 --> 21:42.093
[HAJIME] Oh, right.

21:42.135 --> 21:43.594
The rules.

21:44.262 --> 21:45.972
If I knew their names

21:46.055 --> 21:48.599
and their points,
telling me their strength.

21:49.349 --> 21:51.894
Oh, but points go down
when adding a rule.

21:52.478 --> 21:55.231
So I'd need the number
of rules they added, too.

21:55.815 --> 21:58.985
And knowing which colony
they're in would be valuable.

21:59.026 --> 22:00.236
Kogane.

22:00.278 --> 22:01.361
Add a rule.

22:01.695 --> 22:05.283
Reveal that information
for every player.

22:10.204 --> 22:12.372
[♪ closing theme song playing]

23:41.545 --> 23:44.048
[KENJAKU] You're in the space
between dreams and reality.

23:44.090 --> 23:45.049
It's a curse.

23:45.091 --> 23:46.133
[YUJI]
How do you know my name?

23:46.175 --> 23:47.593
[MEGUMI] I'm not like Itadori.

23:47.718 --> 23:50.388
[KOGANE] Once you step inside,
you, too, become a player.

23:50.428 --> 23:52.430
[MEGUMI] And make them
add a rule to let Tsumiki

23:52.472 --> 23:53.724
escape the Culling Game!
